events.-1000: The Bronze-Age Dong Son culture of the Lac people occupies the Red River valley
events.-300: According to much later sources, the area of present-day Hanoi formed part of the Giao Chỉ region of Van Lang
events.-258: The Âu Việt, united under the Shu emigrant Shu Pan (Thục Phán), invade and conquer Van Lang
events.-214: The First Emperor begins his campaign against the Baiyue (Bách Việt) people of the south
events.-208: Longbian (Long Biên) erected in its eponymous district
events.271: Battle of Jiaozhi between Eastern Wu and the Jin dynasty
events.399: Longbian came under siege from Champa army led by king Bhadravarman I. The siege was relieved later by Chinese reinforcement under the command of Jiaozhou governor Du Yian.
events.454: Songping (Tong Binh) established by the Liu Song on the south bank of the Red River in Hanoi's Tu Liem and Hoai Duc districts
events.544: Long Biên serves as the capital of Ly Bi's realm of Van Xuan
events.621: Longbian and Songping briefly elevated to prefectural status as Longzhou and Songzhou
events.722: Songping falls to Mai Thúc Loan
events.863: Nanzhao captured Hanoi from the Tang dynasty
events.866: Gao Pian, the local jiedushi, expands the fortress at Jincheng and renames it Da Luocheng
events.1010: Luocheng renamed Thang Long with the erection of its Imperial Citadel and dedication as the capital of the Lý dynasty
events.1408: City renamed Dōngguān (Chinese: 東關, 'Eastern Gateway'; Đông Quan in Vietnamese) by the Chinese Ming dynasty
events.1428: City renamed Đông Kinh (Chinese: 東京, as known by Westerners as Tonkin)
events.1615: Trấn Quốc Pagoda relocated to West Lake
events.1730: Trúc Lâm Palace built at Trúc Bạch Lake
events.1831: City renamed Hà Nội (河内, 'Between Rivers' or 'River Interior') by Nguyễn emperor Minh Mạng
events.1873: November 20: Francis Garnier of France takes citadel
events.1945: September 2: Ho Chi Minh reads the Proclamation of Independence of the Democratic Republic of Vietnam in Ba Đình Square
events.1954: City becomes capital of independent North Vietnam
events.1976: City becomes capital of Socialist Republic of Vietnam
events.2000: President of the United States, Bill Clinton, made historic visit to Vietnam in November 2000
events.2001: Trang Tien Plaza (shopping center) in business
events.2003: Mỹ Đình National Stadium opens in Từ Liêm District
events.2006: Vietnam National Convention Center built in Từ Liêm District
events.2008: Hanoi Capital Region created to include 29 districts; population expands to 6,232,940
events.2010: October: Millennial Anniversary of Hanoi. Hanoi Museum opens
